  "texts": [
    "For small learning rate η, we can employ a first-order approximation of the mapping function M around W ðnÞ ij: MðW ij ðnÞ À η dL dW ðnÞ ij Þ≈MðW ij ðn Þ À η dM dW ðnÞ ij dL dW ðnÞ ij, from which follows: δw ðnÞ ij ≈ À η dM dW ðnÞ ij dL dW ðnÞ ij = À η dw ðnÞ ij dW ðnÞ ij \" # 2 dL dw ðnÞ ij, ð10Þ where the second equality comes from plugging in dM dW ðnÞ ij = dw ðnÞ ij dW ðnÞ ij and dL dW ðnÞ ij = dL dw ðnÞ ij dw ðnÞ ij dW ðnÞ ij.",
    "For the α1-model, the difference between the δw ðnÞ ij and a direct ReLU-network update Δw ðnÞ ij = η dL dw ðnÞ ij cannot be corrected with a different learning rate η.",
    "This is due to the fact that the multiplicative bias which appears in Eq.",
    "(10) changes for every neuron pair (i, j) and algorithmic iteration, i.e., dw ðnÞ ij dW ðnÞ ij = dM α dW ðnÞ ij = B ðnÞ i ÀW ðnÞ ij ðB ðnÞ i Þ 2.",
    "Each simulation run was executed on one NVIDIA A100 GPU."
  ],
